1
00:00:12,120 --> 00:00:14,800
{\an8}[Ada] My brother apologises
for not being here

2
00:00:14,880 --> 00:00:17,480
{\an8}and would like to invite all of you
to his home for a meeting.

3
00:00:17,560 --> 00:00:19,960
[Tommy] All you have to do
is sit with Jack Nelson

4
00:00:20,040 --> 00:00:22,040
and talk to him about a new golden age.

5
00:00:22,120 --> 00:00:24,880
-If anyone's going to kill Tommy Shelby...
-It will be you.

6
00:00:24,960 --> 00:00:26,760
<i>The future belongs to us.</i>

7
00:00:26,840 --> 00:00:28,280
Your daughter has consumption.

8
00:00:28,360 --> 00:00:30,720
Consumption is a very infectious disease.

9
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:32,840
[Lizzie] <i>While they are X-raying Ruby,
they have to X-ray us.</i>

10
00:00:32,920 --> 00:00:34,760
It's the girl's mother who laid the curse.

11
00:00:34,840 --> 00:00:36,960
Perhaps she waited
till your little girl was seven.

12
00:00:37,040 --> 00:00:38,400
So you'd know how it feels.

13
00:00:38,480 --> 00:00:40,920
[Tommy] Now that I'm without whiskey,
I can hear the spirits clearly,

14
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:43,360
they are saying Ruby will be well
if I make amends.

15
00:00:43,440 --> 00:00:44,480
She's gone, Tommy.

16
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:53,200
[latch clanks]

17
00:01:06,760 --> 00:01:08,760
["In This Heart" playing]

18
00:01:08,840 --> 00:01:12,520
[woman] <i>♪ In this heart ♪</i>

19
00:01:12,600 --> 00:01:19,200
<i>♪ Lies for you ♪</i>

20
00:01:19,840 --> 00:01:22,200
<i>♪ A lark ♪</i>

21
00:01:22,280 --> 00:01:28,040
<i>♪ Born only for you ♪</i>

22
00:01:28,880 --> 00:01:31,560
<i>♪ Who sings ♪</i>

23
00:01:31,640 --> 00:01:36,920
<i>♪ Only to you ♪</i>

24
00:01:37,560 --> 00:01:44,560
<i>♪ My love, my love, my love ♪</i>

25
00:01:46,160 --> 00:01:52,280
-[woman]<i>♪ I am waiting ♪</i>
-[man] <i>♪ Waiting ♪</i>

26
00:01:52,360 --> 00:01:57,080
-[woman]<i>♪ For you ♪</i>
-[man]<i>♪ For you ♪</i>

27
00:01:57,960 --> 00:02:03,600
-[woman]<i>♪ For only ♪</i>
-[man]<i>♪ For only ♪</i>

28
00:02:03,680 --> 00:02:06,680
-[woman]<i>♪ To adore you ♪</i>
-[man]<i>♪ To adore you ♪</i>

29
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:11,440
-[woman]<i>♪ My heart is for you ♪</i>
-[man]<i>♪ My heart is for you ♪</i>

30
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:18,920
-[woman]<i>♪ My love, my love, my love ♪</i>
-[man]<i>♪ My love, my love, my love ♪</i>

31
00:02:21,280 --> 00:02:26,800
-[woman]<i>♪ This is my grief ♪</i>
-[man]<i>♪ This is my grief ♪</i>

32
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:32,360
-[woman]<i>♪ For you ♪</i>
-[man]<i>♪ For you ♪</i>

33
00:02:33,600 --> 00:02:39,680
-[woman]<i>♪ I will have you ♪</i>
-[man]<i>♪ I will have you ♪</i>

34
00:02:39,760 --> 00:02:44,160
-[woman]<i>♪ With me ♪</i>
-[man]<i>♪ With me ♪</i>

35
00:02:45,560 --> 00:02:52,520
-[woman]<i>♪ In my arms only ♪</i>
-[man]<i>♪ In my arms only ♪</i>

36
00:02:55,080 --> 00:03:00,840
-[woman]<i>♪ For you are only ♪</i>
-[man]<i>♪ For you are only ♪</i>

37
00:03:01,560 --> 00:03:06,800
-[woman]<i>♪ My love, my love ♪</i>
-[man]<i>♪ My love, my love ♪</i>

38
00:03:07,760 --> 00:03:13,400
-[woman]<i>♪ My love ♪</i>
-[man]<i>♪ My love ♪</i>

39
00:03:36,160 --> 00:03:37,200
Arthur.

40
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:41,400
I've written some words.

41
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:44,640
I can't speak 'em.

42
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:46,880
[grunts]

43
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:48,040
You're the oldest.

44
00:03:49,200 --> 00:03:50,400
You speak 'em for me.

45
00:03:59,760 --> 00:04:02,720
[Arthur] I'm sorry, brother.
I can't do it.

46
00:04:04,040 --> 00:04:05,280
[weeping]

47
00:04:21,519 --> 00:04:22,519
[sighs]

48
00:04:33,840 --> 00:04:35,920
We could have afforded a golden carriage.

49
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:42,400
She deserved a golden carriage.

50
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:49,720
But we didn't
afford ourselves that luxury...

51
00:04:53,320 --> 00:04:54,920
because gold doesn't work.

52
00:05:00,960 --> 00:05:03,280
That was the last lesson
that Ruby taught us.

53
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:24,000
This place was her favourite place
in the whole world.

54
00:05:24,080 --> 00:05:25,080
And she used to say,

55
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:27,880
"Dad...

56
00:05:30,960 --> 00:05:33,120
you never know
what's gonna come down the river."

57
00:05:35,440 --> 00:05:36,400
And it's true.

58
00:05:38,920 --> 00:05:40,200
'Cause little Ruby's fate

59
00:05:41,320 --> 00:05:43,120
came a thousand miles too soon.

60
00:05:47,760 --> 00:05:51,720
But in her name
and in her memory, things will change.

61
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:53,120
[sniffles]

62
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:57,920
And whatever comes down
that river from now on,

63
00:05:58,520 --> 00:05:59,800
we will make good...

64
00:06:03,640 --> 00:06:05,880
We will make peaceful and honest and good,

65
00:06:05,960 --> 00:06:08,240
and send it on down the river
better than it was.

66
00:06:08,320 --> 00:06:09,960
In her memory, we will do this.

67
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:17,360
[sniffles]

68
00:06:18,760 --> 00:06:19,840
But for now,

69
00:06:20,880 --> 00:06:21,960
we send her on

70
00:06:23,480 --> 00:06:24,880
to wherever it is you go.

71
00:06:27,080 --> 00:06:29,200
In the hope
that if there is a destination...

72
00:06:31,880 --> 00:06:33,240
...that it's a yard like this.

73
00:06:34,160 --> 00:06:37,680
With horses and boats for her to play on.

74
00:06:49,960 --> 00:06:51,640
[sighs] Tom.

75
00:06:52,760 --> 00:06:54,280
-I've got the petrol.
-[sighs]

76
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:57,120
Who will light the flame?

77
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:03,600
Jeremiah.

78
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:12,960
Jeremiah, you made her laugh.

79
00:07:14,080 --> 00:07:15,240
You light the flame.

80
00:07:15,320 --> 00:07:17,560
No! No!

81
00:07:17,640 --> 00:07:19,480
-Lizzie.
-[Lizzie] No!

82
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:21,800
You won't burn her! No!

83
00:07:21,880 --> 00:07:23,120
Lizzie. [shushes]

84
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:25,280
[Lizzie sobbing]

85
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:31,080
-I just want to see my baby.
-We'll go and see her together. Come on.

86
00:07:31,160 --> 00:07:33,600
-Yeah. Yeah.
-We'll go and see her together.

87
00:07:36,280 --> 00:07:37,240
[sniffles]

88
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:40,840
[exhales]

89
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:46,560
Oh, my baby.

90
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:09,080
The devils who did this will pay, Ruby.

91
00:08:13,240 --> 00:08:14,760
Tommy, what do you mean?

92
00:08:18,320 --> 00:08:19,440
What do you mean?

93
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:22,120
Where're you going?

94
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:06,160
[inaudible]

95
00:09:06,240 --> 00:09:07,600
[dramatic music playing]

96
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,200
[inaudible]

97
00:09:54,680 --> 00:09:55,720
[birds chirping]

98
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:06,040
[vehicle approaching]

99
00:10:11,880 --> 00:10:12,800
[door opens]

100
00:10:14,040 --> 00:10:14,880
[door closes]

101
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:15,960
Riley.

102
00:10:16,760 --> 00:10:18,240
I think the police are here.

103
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:21,720
[Tommy] Evadne Barwell?

104
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:24,160
Yeah.

105
00:10:24,680 --> 00:10:25,680
Who's asking?

106
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:28,960
[Tommy] I'm here on behalf
of the blue sapphire.

107
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:29,960
[gunshots firing]

108
00:10:30,920 --> 00:10:31,840
[people shrieking]

109
00:10:39,440 --> 00:10:41,440
[woman] Don't shoot. There are babies!

110
00:10:41,520 --> 00:10:42,920
Go! Come on.

111
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:44,080
[baby crying]

112
00:10:44,160 --> 00:10:45,680
[woman] We have to go. Come on!

113
00:10:45,760 --> 00:10:47,120
[Tommy breathing heavily]

114
00:10:50,960 --> 00:10:53,200
["Lullaby For Cain" playing]

115
00:11:03,040 --> 00:11:06,600
<i>♪ From the silence ♪</i>

116
00:11:06,680 --> 00:11:10,000
<i>♪ From the night ♪</i>

117
00:11:10,080 --> 00:11:17,040
<i>♪ Comes a distant lullaby ♪</i>

118
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:22,840
<i>♪ Cry, remember that first cry ♪</i>

119
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:26,360
<i>♪ Your brother standing by ♪</i>

120
00:11:26,440 --> 00:11:28,160
<i>♪ And lot... ♪</i>

121
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:29,520
[grunting]

122
00:11:29,600 --> 00:11:32,920
<i>♪ Of loved ♪</i>

123
00:11:33,440 --> 00:11:39,960
<i>♪ Beloved sons of mine ♪</i>

124
00:11:42,920 --> 00:11:48,400
<i>♪ Sing a lullaby ♪</i>

125
00:11:50,480 --> 00:11:56,080
<i>♪ Mother is close by ♪</i>

126
00:11:57,280 --> 00:12:00,200
<i>♪ Innocent eyes ♪</i>

127
00:12:00,680 --> 00:12:05,680
<i>♪ Such innocent eyes ♪</i>

128
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:08,120
[groans]

129
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:13,600
<i>♪ Envy stole your brother's life ♪</i>

130
00:12:14,080 --> 00:12:15,080
<i>♪ Came home... ♪</i>

131
00:12:15,160 --> 00:12:16,120
[sobbing]

132
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:17,240
<i>♪ Murdered ♪</i>

133
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:21,280
<i>♪ Piece of mind ♪</i>

134
00:12:25,320 --> 00:12:26,440
[sobs]

135
00:12:28,360 --> 00:12:34,600
<i>♪ Left you nightmares on the pillow ♪</i>

136
00:12:44,680 --> 00:12:46,160
[engine running]

137
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:54,440
[engine stops]

138
00:12:55,760 --> 00:12:57,040
[sighs deeply]

139
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:07,240
[door closes]

140
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:12,600
Gold dust.

141
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:15,360
Our business is done, Esme.

142
00:13:15,440 --> 00:13:16,880
Get out of the car.

143
00:13:16,960 --> 00:13:18,280
[Esme] Not quite done, Tommy.

144
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:21,240
Thought this'd be a good time.

145
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:23,440
In fact, it's the perfect time.

146
00:13:24,560 --> 00:13:26,360
Some business is still unfinished.

147
00:13:28,280 --> 00:13:31,040
Christians say, "The Lord gives,
the Lord takes away."

148
00:13:31,960 --> 00:13:33,240
Our spirits are the same.

149
00:13:34,240 --> 00:13:36,160
Spirits just took away your child.

150
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:38,240
-Get out of the car, Esme.
-[engine starts]

151
00:13:38,320 --> 00:13:41,040
The same spirits want to
give you a different child, Tommy.

152
00:13:41,840 --> 00:13:43,280
[sighs] What child?

153
00:13:44,520 --> 00:13:45,680
[engine stops]

154
00:13:45,760 --> 00:13:46,840
A daughter lost,

155
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:49,440
a son found.

156
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:55,000
Before you went to France
a long time ago, at Appleby Fair,

157
00:13:55,680 --> 00:13:56,800
you slept with a girl.

158
00:13:57,440 --> 00:13:58,640
Her name was Zelda.

159
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:00,360
I met her.

160
00:14:01,560 --> 00:14:05,240
She said you slept together
under a hazel tree in May 1914.

161
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:10,800
When she fell pregnant
her father threatened to kill you.

162
00:14:11,680 --> 00:14:14,560
But you'd already joined the army
and gone away to France.

163
00:14:18,080 --> 00:14:21,000
You remember the girl
and the hazel tree, don't you, Tommy?

164
00:14:24,880 --> 00:14:27,720
Whoever the boy is, Esme...

165
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:30,440
Whoever he is, our business is done here.

166
00:14:30,520 --> 00:14:34,120
I brought you to this camp for a reason.
And I brought him as well.

167
00:14:35,280 --> 00:14:36,240
He is yours.

168
00:14:37,600 --> 00:14:39,120
A boy born with hazel eyes.

169
00:14:40,400 --> 00:14:41,840
He calls himself Duke.

170
00:14:43,880 --> 00:14:46,360
His mother is dead. He's a thief.

171
00:14:47,040 --> 00:14:48,160
He works the fairground,

172
00:14:48,240 --> 00:14:51,520
but he says he wants more to life
than big wheels and carousels.

173
00:14:55,320 --> 00:14:58,000
If the losing of Ruby's
left a hole in your heart,

174
00:14:59,360 --> 00:15:00,520
I'll send him to you.

175
00:15:02,800 --> 00:15:04,680
If you give me a bit more gold.

176
00:15:06,400 --> 00:15:12,280
I'll tell him Tommy Shelby can offer a man
far more than big wheels and carousels.

177
00:15:12,360 --> 00:15:13,360
[exhales]

178
00:15:14,640 --> 00:15:16,400
Is our business done or not, Tommy?

179
00:15:44,320 --> 00:15:45,880
[Lizzie] I know where you went.

180
00:15:51,080 --> 00:15:52,080
[exhales]

181
00:16:00,160 --> 00:16:02,800
I'll spend more hours working
in the Commons with Mr Churchill.

182
00:16:02,880 --> 00:16:04,000
His fight is my fight.

183
00:16:04,080 --> 00:16:07,280
I sat like a stone and thought about you
killing someone in her name.

184
00:16:07,360 --> 00:16:09,680
The Shelby institutions will be expanded.

185
00:16:11,360 --> 00:16:14,320
I will set up a fund to research
the causes and cures of consumption.

186
00:16:14,400 --> 00:16:16,360
Did the woman you killed have children?

187
00:16:16,440 --> 00:16:18,480
Ten thousand children
die every year, Lizzie.

188
00:16:18,560 --> 00:16:19,440
Go to bed, Tommy.

189
00:16:19,520 --> 00:16:21,080
I've been reading about new research.

190
00:16:21,160 --> 00:16:23,680
-Stop and close your fucking eyes.
-I will not...

191
00:16:23,760 --> 00:16:25,040
I will not stop!

192
00:16:25,120 --> 00:16:27,640
What is this "good" that you will become?!

193
00:16:30,400 --> 00:16:31,360
[exhales]

194
00:16:38,160 --> 00:16:39,200
I killed a woman.

195
00:16:40,920 --> 00:16:42,680
I killed a woman and three men.

196
00:16:42,760 --> 00:16:46,640
And their bodies will be thrown
aboard the boat like all the other bodies.

197
00:16:46,720 --> 00:16:49,720
But I am stepping off that boat
and onto another boat.

198
00:16:51,280 --> 00:16:52,360
Do you understand?!

199
00:16:55,560 --> 00:16:56,480
Yeah.

200
00:17:08,520 --> 00:17:10,599
The doctor from the sanatorium called

201
00:17:10,680 --> 00:17:13,160
and said that he needs
to speak with you urgently.

202
00:17:14,880 --> 00:17:17,359
But I think you're now
beyond the help of doctors.

203
00:17:17,440 --> 00:17:18,280
Lizzie...

204
00:17:19,160 --> 00:17:20,480
[Lizzie breathing heavily]

205
00:17:21,560 --> 00:17:23,240
Frances said Arthur's here.

206
00:17:24,760 --> 00:17:25,680
[door slams]

207
00:17:47,720 --> 00:17:48,560
[switch flicks]

208
00:17:56,080 --> 00:17:57,000
[Arthur] Tommy?

209
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:00,680
-Tom?
-[Tommy] Yeah, it's me.

210
00:18:02,080 --> 00:18:03,080
[Arthur] Ah, fuck.

211
00:18:21,520 --> 00:18:22,640
[Tommy exhales]

212
00:18:22,720 --> 00:18:24,400
Arthur, give me a light, will you?

213
00:18:25,560 --> 00:18:26,720
I can't find my lighter.

214
00:18:28,960 --> 00:18:29,800
[exhales]

215
00:18:31,560 --> 00:18:33,080
[sniffs]

216
00:18:39,720 --> 00:18:42,200
Sorry I didn't speak at the wagon, Tom.

217
00:18:52,160 --> 00:18:53,280
Don't be sorry.

218
00:18:56,800 --> 00:18:58,040
What are you doing here?

219
00:19:01,120 --> 00:19:03,760
Waiting for this fucking cup to fill up.

220
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:09,560
Nearly empty, this barrel.

221
00:19:10,040 --> 00:19:11,200
[scoffs]

222
00:19:11,280 --> 00:19:13,160
Plenty of barrels, Arthur.

223
00:19:14,560 --> 00:19:15,760
Start another barrel.

224
00:19:16,760 --> 00:19:19,320
I thought maybe
they were all full of fucking blood.

225
00:19:19,400 --> 00:19:20,400
[breathes deeply]

226
00:19:23,240 --> 00:19:24,400
The junk, Tom.

227
00:19:26,680 --> 00:19:28,160
Fucks up your mind.

228
00:19:32,840 --> 00:19:33,960
You know, Arthur,

229
00:19:36,640 --> 00:19:38,280
you was already fucked up.

230
00:19:38,840 --> 00:19:39,760
[exhales]

231
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:43,080
[Tommy] You was fucked up
since you was a kid.

232
00:19:45,560 --> 00:19:46,520
This is my theory.

233
00:19:48,840 --> 00:19:49,680
[clicks tongue]

234
00:19:50,840 --> 00:19:53,240
It's from that time I gave you a beating,

235
00:19:53,320 --> 00:19:55,200
when you was 12 and I was nine.

236
00:19:56,560 --> 00:19:58,360
We were fighting over cigarettes.

237
00:20:01,280 --> 00:20:05,360
Maybe while I had you down on the ground,

238
00:20:06,480 --> 00:20:08,400
I gave you one too many to the head.

239
00:20:09,120 --> 00:20:10,960
It was a draw, though, Tom.

240
00:20:11,480 --> 00:20:12,480
Nah.

241
00:20:14,120 --> 00:20:15,200
I beat you.

242
00:20:16,320 --> 00:20:17,480
I had you pinned.

243
00:20:18,040 --> 00:20:19,240
You actually didn't.

244
00:20:20,720 --> 00:20:21,600
[chuckles softly]

245
00:20:21,680 --> 00:20:22,960
We both agreed.

246
00:20:23,040 --> 00:20:25,320
You're so fucked,
you can't remember, brother.

247
00:20:27,520 --> 00:20:28,440
I do.

248
00:20:28,800 --> 00:20:30,760
I do remember these little things.

249
00:20:31,280 --> 00:20:32,400
[Tommy] I know you do.

250
00:20:33,720 --> 00:20:34,840
So do I.

251
00:20:36,080 --> 00:20:37,960
The fog and the gas is clearing, eh?

252
00:20:50,160 --> 00:20:51,080
[coughs]

253
00:21:10,760 --> 00:21:11,640
[lighter clicks]

254
00:21:29,960 --> 00:21:32,080
Your cup's nearly full, pass it here.

255
00:21:36,720 --> 00:21:37,800
But, Tommy...

256
00:21:38,440 --> 00:21:39,280
[exhales]

257
00:21:40,920 --> 00:21:42,520
