553
00:44:35,280 --> 00:44:38,520
<i>♪ Well, I try
I do, I really try ♪</i>

554
00:44:39,200 --> 00:44:42,280
<i>♪ But I just err, baby
I do, I error ♪</i>

555
00:44:43,000 --> 00:44:46,560
<i>♪ So come and find me
My darling one ♪</i>

556
00:44:46,640 --> 00:44:49,880
<i>♪ I'm down to the grounds
The very dregs ♪</i>

557
00:44:50,440 --> 00:44:53,440
<i>♪ Here she comes
Blocking the sun ♪</i>

558
00:44:53,920 --> 00:44:57,240
<i>♪ Blood running down
The inside of her legs ♪</i>

559
00:44:57,800 --> 00:45:01,040
<i>♪ The moon in the sky
Is battered and mangled ♪</i>

560
00:45:01,120 --> 00:45:02,800
<i>♪ And the bells in the chapel ♪</i>

561
00:45:02,880 --> 00:45:06,800
<i>♪ Go jingle-jangle
Jingle-jangle ♪</i>

562
00:45:06,880 --> 00:45:09,880
<i>♪ Jingle-jangle
Jingle-jangle ♪</i>

563
00:45:09,960 --> 00:45:13,520
<i>♪ Do you love me? ♪</i>

564
00:45:19,120 --> 00:45:20,200
[banging on door]

565
00:45:20,320 --> 00:45:22,440
<i>♪ Do you love me? ♪</i>

566
00:45:25,840 --> 00:45:27,120
I saw him leave.

567
00:45:29,040 --> 00:45:32,240
He keeps this apartment
expressly for this purpose, doesn't he?

568
00:45:32,320 --> 00:45:33,280
[door closes]

569
00:45:34,480 --> 00:45:36,320
Are you following me, Mr Shelby?

570
00:45:37,560 --> 00:45:38,640
I'm flattered.

571
00:45:39,360 --> 00:45:40,320
But why?

572
00:45:41,480 --> 00:45:42,920
When I do business with someone,

573
00:45:43,000 --> 00:45:45,640
I make it my business
to know their secrets.

574
00:45:48,560 --> 00:45:50,640
Mosley's reputation is no secret.

575
00:45:51,480 --> 00:45:52,680
Not him, you.

576
00:45:53,480 --> 00:45:54,320
[lighter clicks]

577
00:45:55,880 --> 00:45:57,480
How did you know I'd come here?

578
00:45:58,360 --> 00:45:59,560
I know things.

579
00:46:00,760 --> 00:46:02,640
I read people's minds, you know...

580
00:46:05,760 --> 00:46:09,040
Little glances across tables. It's a gift.

581
00:46:09,120 --> 00:46:10,160
The whole family.

582
00:46:11,320 --> 00:46:13,120
Witches and sorcerers.

583
00:46:22,440 --> 00:46:24,040
Your uncle will disown you.

584
00:46:25,440 --> 00:46:27,680
Fucking his business partner
behind his back.

585
00:46:27,760 --> 00:46:28,600
[Gina laughs]

586
00:46:29,400 --> 00:46:30,960
You think he has morals?

587
00:46:31,040 --> 00:46:31,920
He's a Catholic.

588
00:46:32,000 --> 00:46:34,480
Men do what they want,
women do what they are told.

589
00:46:36,960 --> 00:46:38,080
Will you tell Michael?

590
00:46:39,680 --> 00:46:40,840
Michael is family.

591
00:46:42,240 --> 00:46:43,960
We are a family healed.

592
00:46:45,920 --> 00:46:47,560
You have no interest in me

593
00:46:48,200 --> 00:46:49,360
or in Michael.

594
00:46:51,280 --> 00:46:53,920
So why don't you just tell me
what you actually want?

595
00:47:02,240 --> 00:47:03,080
[exhales]

596
00:47:05,840 --> 00:47:09,800
You will be with Mosley
when he's in Berlin.

597
00:47:11,160 --> 00:47:15,120
You'll be in the room when he meets
senior members of the German government.

598
00:47:15,200 --> 00:47:16,920
I want to know what is discussed.

599
00:47:18,440 --> 00:47:20,280
And I want to know what is decided.

600
00:47:22,960 --> 00:47:24,080
And if I lie?

601
00:47:26,560 --> 00:47:27,560
I will know.

602
00:47:36,920 --> 00:47:38,920
You know, Michael thinks you're the Devil.

603
00:47:40,560 --> 00:47:42,560
And I think he might actually be right.

604
00:47:44,480 --> 00:47:46,360
That's the other reason I came here.

605
00:47:47,120 --> 00:47:50,040
What are Michael's real intentions
towards me, Gina?

606
00:47:51,080 --> 00:47:52,600
And if you lie, I will know.

607
00:47:58,200 --> 00:48:02,400
Tommy, he intends to complete the deal.

608
00:48:04,200 --> 00:48:05,640
And then you both walk away.

609
00:48:11,680 --> 00:48:12,600
[chuckles softly]

610
00:48:17,840 --> 00:48:18,720
[door closes]

611
00:48:20,440 --> 00:48:21,440
Fuck.

612
00:48:28,320 --> 00:48:29,200
[pen drops]

613
00:48:29,840 --> 00:48:30,800
[sighs]

614
00:49:24,760 --> 00:49:25,680
[exhales]

615
00:49:28,600 --> 00:49:29,640
[fly buzzes]

616
00:49:41,640 --> 00:49:43,200
[knock on door]

617
00:49:43,720 --> 00:49:44,720
Come.

618
00:49:47,360 --> 00:49:49,160
Mr Shelby, Dr Holford.

619
00:49:52,360 --> 00:49:53,400
Send him in.

620
00:50:00,760 --> 00:50:02,680
You said it had to be in person.

621
00:50:03,400 --> 00:50:04,400
Here I am.

622
00:50:06,320 --> 00:50:07,680
You might want to sit down.

623
00:50:13,800 --> 00:50:14,640
[sighs]

624
00:50:15,240 --> 00:50:18,480
Mr Shelby, I know that you are
still grieving for your daughter,

625
00:50:20,040 --> 00:50:21,720
but I have news that cannot wait.

626
00:50:26,880 --> 00:50:31,840
When you were X-rayed and examined
at the sanatorium, ten days ago,

627
00:50:34,280 --> 00:50:37,160
there was no TB found in your lung.

628
00:50:39,680 --> 00:50:41,800
But I am afraid they found something else.

629
00:50:42,880 --> 00:50:45,160
Something related
to your daughter's illness.

630
00:50:49,040 --> 00:50:51,160
They tried
to speak to you at the hospital,

631
00:50:52,040 --> 00:50:53,560
but you were not cooperating.

632
00:50:55,200 --> 00:50:56,680
After your daughter's death,

633
00:50:58,160 --> 00:51:00,520
you could not be found
to be informed in person.

634
00:51:01,800 --> 00:51:05,080
Eventually, as your personal doctor,
they called me.

635
00:51:08,600 --> 00:51:11,280
I didn't offer you tea.
You look like death. Do you want tea?

636
00:51:13,240 --> 00:51:14,160
No.

637
00:51:16,160 --> 00:51:18,800
At the sanatorium,
they conducted blood tests.

638
00:51:20,920 --> 00:51:24,240
The tests suggest
that the shadow you can see

639
00:51:24,320 --> 00:51:28,160
at the base of your skull is not cancer.

640
00:51:29,520 --> 00:51:30,920
It is tuberculoma.

641
00:51:33,400 --> 00:51:36,960
A tubercular growth
caused by the same bacteria as TB.

642
00:51:40,800 --> 00:51:43,040
You may have picked it up
from your daughter.

643
00:51:44,760 --> 00:51:48,120
Once this disease
enters a household, it can run wild.

644
00:51:49,200 --> 00:51:51,640
It can be transmitted with a simple kiss.

645
00:51:55,800 --> 00:51:58,320
It seems the Shelby household
is no exception.

646
00:52:02,520 --> 00:52:06,440
Mr Shelby, as I say,
I am aware that you are still grieving.

647
00:52:07,840 --> 00:52:10,320
But you must understand
this is very serious.

648
00:52:12,640 --> 00:52:15,680
From the size of the tumour,
expansion must have been rapid.

649
00:52:17,160 --> 00:52:20,920
I have no doubt that you are
already experiencing symptoms.

650
00:52:22,640 --> 00:52:24,560
Have you recently suffered seizures?

651
00:52:26,080 --> 00:52:27,640
Bouts of weakness?

652
00:52:28,280 --> 00:52:31,520
Dissociation? Hallucinations?

653
00:52:39,240 --> 00:52:41,360
-[grunts]
-Why didn't you come and see me?

654
00:52:44,160 --> 00:52:45,520
I have work to do.

655
00:52:49,240 --> 00:52:50,440
Am I a danger to others?

656
00:52:52,520 --> 00:52:53,360
No.

657
00:52:54,240 --> 00:52:56,880
Unlike TB, tuberculoma is not infectious.

658
00:52:58,000 --> 00:53:01,840
Mr Shelby, it is not infectious,

659
00:53:01,920 --> 00:53:06,480
but in your case,
I am afraid it is inoperable.

660
00:53:08,320 --> 00:53:10,120
The growth is in your brainstem.

661
00:53:10,200 --> 00:53:13,880
Any attempt to remove it would result
in trauma and brain haemorrhage.

662
00:53:18,640 --> 00:53:20,360
Whilst you were refusing my calls,

663
00:53:20,440 --> 00:53:23,720
I showed your X-rays to three
of the best surgeons in the country.

664
00:53:27,880 --> 00:53:29,760
They all said they would not operate.

665
00:53:31,160 --> 00:53:32,480
That it would be futile.

666
00:53:34,160 --> 00:53:38,160
Of course, you will want
a second opinion for yourself.

667
00:53:39,560 --> 00:53:42,320
Dr Helen Rutherford at St Thomas'.

668
00:53:42,880 --> 00:53:43,880
She is a friend.

669
00:53:48,480 --> 00:53:49,360
[clears throat]

670
00:53:55,360 --> 00:53:56,320
This...

671
00:53:58,680 --> 00:53:59,920
How bad will it get?

672
00:54:06,520 --> 00:54:07,800
As the tumour grows,

673
00:54:08,880 --> 00:54:12,400
the rate of physical
and mental deterioration will increase.

674
00:54:17,120 --> 00:54:21,040
Eventually, you will need
people around you constantly

675
00:54:22,040 --> 00:54:23,600
who love you very much.

676
00:54:27,080 --> 00:54:28,000
How long?

677
00:54:31,880 --> 00:54:35,000
I understand that you have
defeated many enemies, Mr Shelby.

678
00:54:36,280 --> 00:54:37,520
Now you have a new one.

679
00:54:38,560 --> 00:54:39,560
Inside you.

680
00:54:41,240 --> 00:54:42,560
You cannot defeat it.

681
00:54:44,160 --> 00:54:46,120
But you can keep it at bay for a while.

682
00:54:47,000 --> 00:54:50,920
If you live correctly,
if you are determined, and if you fight...

683
00:54:51,000 --> 00:54:54,800
I asked you a question.
So I want an answer.

684
00:54:54,880 --> 00:54:56,680
I don't want your fucking platitudes.

685
00:54:57,760 --> 00:55:02,160
How long before I need people around me
who love me very much?

686
00:55:02,840 --> 00:55:03,680
[door opens]

687
00:55:07,080 --> 00:55:08,960
-Sorry.
-[Tommy] It's fine, Lizzie.

688
00:55:09,040 --> 00:55:10,840
My accountant here was just leaving.

689
00:55:15,480 --> 00:55:16,440
[clears throat]

690
00:55:16,520 --> 00:55:18,960
I will telephone you
when I get back to London.

691
00:55:19,040 --> 00:55:20,160
No, don't have enough time.

692
00:55:20,240 --> 00:55:22,560
You're an accountant,
give me a fucking number now.

693
00:55:24,560 --> 00:55:25,560
[Holford] One year.

694
00:55:26,960 --> 00:55:28,200
Perhaps 18 months.

695
00:55:28,760 --> 00:55:31,760
[clicks tongue] That's fine.
That's all I need to know.

696
00:55:31,840 --> 00:55:34,720
I will adjust
my finances accordingly. Thank you.

697
00:55:37,120 --> 00:55:39,120
I will write you,
explaining the full implications.

698
00:55:39,200 --> 00:55:40,320
Yep, thank you.

699
00:55:44,800 --> 00:55:45,760
Good day.

700
00:55:54,520 --> 00:55:55,800
Something serious?

701
00:55:57,080 --> 00:55:58,640
No. No, just a...

702
00:56:00,000 --> 00:56:02,240
Just a bill I wasn't expecting, and I...

703
00:56:03,680 --> 00:56:04,800
I'll have to pay it.

704
00:56:15,040 --> 00:56:17,160
Can you give me
a minute on my own, Lizzie?

705
00:56:21,160 --> 00:56:22,120
Yeah.

706
00:56:30,960 --> 00:56:31,800
[door closes]

707
00:56:37,920 --> 00:56:38,920
I'm not a devil.

708
00:56:42,360 --> 00:56:44,000
Just an ordinary, mortal man.

709
00:56:50,920 --> 00:56:53,360
[Polly] <i>There will be a war in this family</i>

710
00:56:55,320 --> 00:56:56,920
<i>and one of you will die.</i>

711
00:56:59,800 --> 00:57:00,640
[Tommy] Polly...

712
00:57:02,920 --> 00:57:05,360
Just give me enough time
to do what I have to do.

713
00:57:07,680 --> 00:57:11,040
[Polly] <i>Kill and kill...</i>

